events at low energy

00:16:27.950 --> 00:16:31.860
because you have these
constituents of quarks

00:16:31.860 --> 00:16:33.180
and gluons which collide.

00:16:33.180 --> 00:16:35.742
By going up in energy you
also produce a lot more Higgs

00:16:35.742 --> 00:16:36.700
particles, for example.

00:16:36.700 --> 00:16:39.520
In fact some small
factor of energy

00:16:39.520 --> 00:16:42.440
gives you one or two orders of
magnitude more Higgs particles

00:16:42.440 --> 00:16:42.940
per second.

00:16:42.940 --> 00:16:47.360
So you gain in the energy reach,
and you also gain at low energy

00:16:47.360 --> 00:16:48.180
when you include.

00:16:48.180 --> 00:16:49.510
